Bunyala residents have been cautioned to stop feasting at funerals after 27 people fell ill in a cholera outbreak. Deputy county commissioner Titus Kilonzi (pictured) urged the residents to maintain hygiene in their homes. “Stop the habit of eating at funerals, especially now the Public Health department officials have reported 27 cholera cases in the subcounty,” he said. Kilonzi spoke at Budalang’i High School during Madaraka Day celebrations on Friday. On politics, he urged Budalang’i MP Raphael Wanjala and his predecessor Ababu Namwamba to end their political differences and maintain peace for the sake of development.